    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.17.23"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">23</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>A wreath with a bow surrounding the letter W</figDesc>
                        <p>W</p>
                    </figure>
                
                    <hi rend="caps">THE WILLARD HOTEL
                        <lb/>
                    WASHINGTON. D.C.</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Nov. 20th, 1937</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                            <addrLine>Branson</addrLine>
                                <addrLine>Missouri:</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Sir:</salute></opener> <p>There has recently come into my possession a copy of your book: Black Elk Speaks.</p>
                
                <p>I have read that book with intense interest&#8212; parts of it several times. It is a book of wonderful value to those who understand its revealations<sic>revelations</sic></p>
                
                <p>I understand the psychice<sic>psychic</sic> aspect of it; that to me is its main value. It is remarkable.</p>
                
                <p>I wish the book could be repubtished<sic>republished</sic>, minus the war and killig aspects. Is the book still in print?</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours Truly</salute> <signed>Wm H. Burr</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
